author: @Chocapic_13
text: Hey josh, I love your videos, but is there any reason why you prefer random forests over gradient boosting applied to decision trees? They're both very easy to analyse, but gradient boosting has better results for prediction, if not the best across all algorithms for structured data. For example the CatBoost library has a ton of built-in functions to analyze your data after fitting a model.

author: @livingwithlinlin3122
text: Professor, Thank you so much for spending so much time making the video to share your knowledge with us. I was extremely moved after watching the answer for comment#3. The most recent video I watched from your channel is gradient descent step by step. In fact I only watched 50% of it and got stuck on "derivative". I learned calculus over 25 years ago, in Chinese, and never get to use calculus after that. I was so clueless about the word "derivative" and did not consider it as a term in math at the beginning. lol. After googling and relearning through Khan Academy, I finally start understanding it and made my daughter who learned AP Calculus AB watch your video and confirm on my understanding.  It feels good when stuff started connecting to each other. :-)  Hopefully I can catch your next live streaming.
